However, Democrats are now opposing a clean continuing resolution and will continue to oppose any federal spending bill that strays from the deal already announced.

description:

Ben discusses the big problem for Democrats after the election: Should they slip more to the left or move back more to the center? Their battle for the democratic left is very much alive, and it is being discussed that they need to start being led by a younger demographic. Ben also talks about the bipartisan deal on the floor to keep the government funded through mid-March and provide more than $100 Billion in relief to disaster victims and farmers. House Republicans are ticked off at what is just another “pork bill,” but it needs to pass so the government is funded when Trump comes into office. Trump does not want a government shutdown on the table when he enters office. He would prefer the government to be funded through March and then use his power to get wavering Republicans to sign on to bills.
